dc_title_s: Loudunois, Laudunam / Mirebalais /Amstelodami Exudebat Joannes Janssonius
dc_description_s: 2 maps on 1 sheet 45 x55 cm.|Relief shown pictorially.|Mirebalais map attaches to the southern portion of main map and north orients to the left side of the Mirebalais map.|Title cartouche is surrounded by children with baskets of grapes and cheese.|This state was published in atlases by Jan Jansson in 1636, 1637, and 1680.|From the Jansson Appendix Atlas 1636-1680, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan.
